    {q:"In suspected CAUTI, what is the correct sequence of catheter management, culturing, and antibiotic selection?", options:["Remove/replace the catheter first, then culture, then treat with the narrowest effective (culture-guided) antibiotic","Start broad-spectrum antibiotics immediately, then culture, then remove the catheter last","Culture through the existing catheter first, then remove it only if the culture is positive","Treat empirically with antifungals before catheter removal in all cases"], answer:0, explain:"For CAUTI, the catheter should be removed or replaced before culturing, and then the narrowest effective (definitive, culture-guided) antibiotic should be chosen — broad empiric therapy is not the default approach here.", ref:10}
